---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'bupa-global', text: 'Bupa Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'aetna-international', text: 'Aetna International', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'senior-needs', text: 'What Seniors Need to Consider', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Aetna International Review', href: '/providers/aetna-international' },
  { title: 'Retiree Insurance', href: '/insurance-for/retirees' },
  { title: 'Pre-Existing Conditions', href: '/guides/pre-existing-conditions-abroad' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'aetna', header: 'Aetna International' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Age Limit (New)', cigna: '74', bupa: '85+', aetna: '64' },
  { feature: 'Lifetime Renewal', cigna: 'Yes', bupa: 'Yes', aetna: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Pre-existing Handling', cigna: 'Strict', bupa: 'More Flexible', aetna: 'Moderate' },
  { feature: 'Coverage Limit', cigna: 'Unlimited', bupa: 'Unlimited', aetna: '$5M' },
  { feature: 'Chronic Conditions', cigna: 'If underwritten', bupa: 'Better options', aetna: 'If underwritten' },
  { feature: 'No-Claims Discount', cigna: 'No', bupa: 'Yes', aetna: 'No' },
  { feature: 'US Coverage', cigna: 'Optional', bupa: 'Optional', aetna: 'Best' },
  { feature: 'Best For', cigna: 'Under 65', bupa: 'Over 65', aetna: 'US-connected' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'aetna', header: 'Aetna International' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 55', bupa: '$600-900/mo', cigna: '$550-850/mo', aetna: '$500-750/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 60', bupa: '$800-1,200/mo', cigna: '$750-1,100/mo', aetna: '$700-1,000/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 65', bupa: '$1,100-1,600/mo', cigna: '$1,000-1,500/mo', aetna: 'Age limit' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 60', bupa: '$1,400-2,100/mo', cigna: '$1,300-1,900/mo', aetna: '$1,200-1,800/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Bupa vs Cigna vs Aetna: Best Insurance for Senior Expats 2026"
  description="Compare health insurance for senior expats (50-70+): Bupa Global, Cigna Global, and Aetna International. Age limits, pre-existing conditions, and pricing for older adults abroad."
  headline="Bupa vs Cigna vs Aetna: Senior Expat Insurance Compared"
  subheadline="Insurance gets harder after 50. Age limits, higher premiums, and stricter underwriting. Here's which insurers work best for senior expats."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <h2 id="quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-purple-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best for 65+</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Highest age acceptance (85+). Lifetime renewal. Most flexible on pre-existing conditions. Best for older seniors.</p>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-2 border-primary-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Service</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Best app and network. Accepts to age 74. Good for active seniors who want premium service.</p>
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">US Network</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Aetna International</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Best US coverage. Age limit 64 for new members. Good for younger seniors with US ties.</p>
      <a href="/go/aetna-international" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Aetna Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    Insurance for seniors is more complex: age limits for new applicants, higher premiums, stricter underwriting, and more pre-existing conditions to navigate. Bupa accepts the oldest applicants and is most flexible on conditions. Cigna offers the best service up to age 74. Aetna is limited to under 65 but has the best US coverage.
  </p>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="bupa-global">Bupa Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best for 65+</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Lifetime Renewal</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">No-Claims Discount</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Bupa Global is the standout choice for senior expats, especially those over 65. They accept new applicants up to age 85+ (plan dependent), offer lifetime renewal regardless of health changes, and are more flexible on pre-existing conditions than competitors.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Highest age acceptance for new applicants (85+)</li>
    <li>Lifetime renewal guarantee—can't be dropped</li>
    <li>More flexible pre-existing condition handling</li>
    <li>No-claims discount (rewards healthy years)</li>
    <li>Excellent customer service for complex needs</li>
    <li>Unlimited coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Most expensive option</li>
    <li>Premium increases with age</li>
    <li>App not as polished as Cigna</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Seniors over 65. Those with pre-existing conditions. Anyone who wants lifetime renewal protection. Long-term expats planning to age abroad.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/bupa-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="cigna-global">Cigna Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Service</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best App</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Up to Age 74</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Cigna Global offers the best service and digital experience, accepting new applicants up to age 74. For healthy seniors under 75 who want premium coverage with the best app and fastest claims, Cigna delivers. Strict on pre-existing conditions though.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Best mobile app and digital experience</li>
    <li>Largest provider network (1.5M+)</li>
    <li>Fast claims processing</li>
    <li>Accepts up to age 74 for new members</li>
    <li>Lifetime renewal once accepted</li>
    <li>Unlimited coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Age 74 cutoff for new applicants</li>
    <li>Strict pre-existing condition underwriting</li>
    <li>No no-claims discount</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Active seniors under 75 who want premium service. Those with few pre-existing conditions. Tech-savvy seniors who value app convenience.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="aetna-international">Aetna International</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">US Network</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Under 65</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">CVS Integration</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Aetna International is limited to applicants under 65 but excels for those with US connections. The CVS/Aetna network means excellent US coverage for visits home. Good for younger seniors (50-64) who split time between abroad and the US.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Best US coverage (CVS/Aetna network)</li>
    <li>Good for seniors with US family/property</li>
    <li>$5M coverage limit</li>
    <li>Competitive pricing for under-65</li>
    <li>Good claims experience</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Age 64 limit for new applicants</li>
    <li>Limited lifetime renewal guarantees</li>
    <li>Smaller international network</li>
    <li>Not available for 65+</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Younger seniors (50-64) with US connections. Those who visit the US frequently. Seniors who may eventually return to the US.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/aetna-international" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Aetna Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/aetna-international" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Senior-Friendly Quotes"
    description="Coverage for older adults requires specialized quotes. Get accurate pricing for your age and health situation."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing Comparison</h2>

  <p>
    Premiums increase significantly with age. A 65-year-old pays roughly double what a 45-year-old pays. Budget for $800-1,600/month for comprehensive senior coverage.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
    *Estimated ranges for comprehensive coverage excluding US. Prices increase with age. Pre-existing conditions may add premium loading.
  </p>

  <h2 id="senior-needs">What Senior Expats Need to Consider</h2>

  <h3>Age Limits for New Applicants</h3>
  <p>
    This is the biggest barrier for seniors:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Aetna:</strong> 64 maximum for new applicants</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> 74 maximum for new applicants</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa:</strong> 85+ on some plans (most flexible)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Once accepted, lifetime renewal usually applies—you won't be dropped. But getting accepted initially becomes harder with age.
  </p>

  <h3>Pre-Existing Conditions</h3>
  <p>
    Most seniors have some conditions. Here's how insurers handle them:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Bupa:</strong> Most flexible—more likely to cover with waiting period or loading</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Strict—more likely to exclude conditions permanently</li>
    <li><strong>Aetna:</strong> Moderate—case-by-case underwriting</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Lifetime Renewal</h3>
  <p>
    Critical for seniors: can the insurer drop you if you develop conditions?
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Bupa:</strong> Strongest guarantee—can't be dropped for health reasons</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Lifetime renewal once accepted</li>
    <li><strong>Aetna:</strong> More limited—review policy terms carefully</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>No-Claims Discounts</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa offers no-claims discounts—premiums reduce if you don't claim. Rewards healthy seniors. Cigna and Aetna don't offer this.
  </p>

  <h3>Medicare and International Insurance</h3>
  <p>
    US Medicare doesn't cover you abroad. Senior Americans abroad need international insurance. If you return to the US, you'll need to enroll in Medicare (with potential late penalties if you wait).
  </p>

  <h2 id="best-for">Which Is Best For You?</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Bupa Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are over 65</li>
        <li>Have pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>Want guaranteed lifetime renewal</li>
        <li>Plan to stay abroad long-term</li>
        <li>Value no-claims discounts</li>
        <li>Need the most flexible underwriting</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are under 75</li>
        <li>Are relatively healthy with few conditions</li>
        <li>Want the best app and service</li>
        <li>Value fast claims processing</li>
        <li>Need the largest provider network</li>
        <li>Prioritize digital experience</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Aetna International if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are under 65</li>
        <li>Have strong US connections</li>
        <li>Visit the US regularly</li>
        <li>Might return to the US eventually</li>
        <li>Want the best US network access</li>
        <li>Need CVS/Aetna integration</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>What if I'm over 75 and need insurance?</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa is your best option—they accept applicants well into their 80s on some plans. If Bupa declines, consider local insurance in your country of residence, or work with a specialist broker who can access niche markets.
  </p>

  <h3>Will my premiums keep increasing every year?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, premiums increase with age. Expect 5-15% annual increases due to age alone. Medical inflation adds more. Budget for increasing costs as you age. Bupa's no-claims discount helps offset some increase.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I develop a serious condition after being insured?</h3>
  <p>
    Conditions that develop while insured are covered—that's the whole point. Lifetime renewal means you can't be dropped. This is why getting insured while healthy matters so much.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I use Medicare and international insurance together?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, but they serve different purposes. Medicare covers you in the US only. International insurance covers you abroad. Some seniors maintain both—Medicare for US visits, international for their home abroad.
  </p>

  <h3>What about long-term care coverage?</h3>
  <p>
    International health insurance doesn't typically cover long-term care (nursing homes, assisted living). That's a separate product. If you anticipate needing long-term care, plan for it separately.
  </p>

  <h3>Is it too late to get coverage if I already have conditions?</h3>
  <p>
    Not necessarily. Bupa is most likely to cover you with pre-existing conditions—perhaps with exclusions, waiting periods, or premium loading. It's worth applying. Some coverage is better than none.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Senior insurance is complex. Age limits, pre-existing condition handling, and renewal terms vary. This comparison provides general guidance—get personalized quotes and read policy terms carefully before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
